						<summary>

						<p>This is merely dated as Sādhāraṇa, Puraṭṭāśi 26, and records a solemn oath (<hi rend="italic">mariyādi-muṟi</hi>) given by the <hi rend="italic">sthānikas</hi> and staff of the temple at Tirunāmakkal to one Svāmināyakkar-Ayyaṉ (or before God ?) that they would not misappropriate any gifts received towards offerings to the deity.</p>						

